Topic: Implement a Linked List in Python Using OOP and Delete the Nth Node
Task: Create a Python program that implements a singly linked list using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles. 
Your implementation should include the following: A Node class to represent each node in the list. A LinkedList class to manage the nodes, 
with methods to: Add a node to the end of the list Print the list Delete the nth node (where n is a 1-based index) Include exception handling 
to manage edge cases such as: Deleting a node from an empty list Deleting a node with an index out of range Test your implementation with at least one sample list.
